Interface HTML5Input

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    BoundedInput<T>, MultipleInput, RangedInput<N>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractCalendarMultiInput, AbstractDateInput, AppUserFactory.AppUserNameInput, CalendarFieldInput, CalendarMonthInput, CalendarMultiInputWrapper, DataObjectFactory.DataObjectInput, DataObjectFactory.DataObjectIntegerInput, DataObjectFactory.SortingDataObjectInput, DateInput, DayMultiInput, DoubleInput, EmailInput, EmailListInput, EnumIntegerInput, IntegerInput, IntegerRangeInput, IntegerSetInput, LongInput, MonthInput, MonthMultiInput, NumberInput, PercentInput, PhoneInput, RangeDateInput, RealInput, RelativeDateInput, TimeStampInput, TimeStampMultiInput, URLInput

    public interface HTML5Input
    An Interface for Inputs that can represented as html5 inputs. This does not change the behaviour of the input but does assert compatibility (or not) with a corresponding html-5 input type.
    Author:
    spb

    • Method Detail

      • getType

        java.lang.String getType()
        get the type tag to emit for the corresponding html5 type. If this method returns null no type should be used. This is for the case where. a sub-class breaks compatibility and needs to supress a type set in a superclass.
        Returns:
        name or null;
